10.25.23  2:40 am   i was looking for the prime factorization of 1945 in my head and i'm just doing it naively. took 5 out so i was at 389*5, but then i checked everything up to 41 before going "yeah maybe 389 is prime" and calling it a day, but idk really. is there a quick way to make sure?

      you don't have to go any further than the square root. for example, you actually didn't have to check any higher than 23 because 23 squared is in the 500s which is already higher than 389. this technique works as long as you checked everything below it and didn't make any mistakes

10.24.23  1:40 pm   somebody told me i've gotta learn a bunch of scales. what the fuck, man? i want to play what i want to play.

     that's fine. that's legal, i think

     i want to play what i'm in the mood to play-how do i start necoming good at playing what's in my head, not what's on the page? 

     well first of all, just don't use pages. but then you're gonna have to start gradually building neural connections in your brain so you have an intuitive idea of what each note would or would not do, at any given time. and, like learning a language, this happens naturally as you spend more and more and more time with an instrument, and enjoying it. you just need to spend a large large amount of time having fun and being curious. that's it
